        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "JulianDateToYYYYMMDD",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a Julian date format into the standard Gregorian date format (YYYYMMDD). Julian dates are often used in legacy systems and certain industries for date representation, and this function facilitates the conversion to a more universally recognized date format."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
